cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

This paper is about designing deep neural network architectures using reinforcement learning and exploring the architecture space efficiently. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of function-preserving transformations, which suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to image benchmark datasets, indicating a potential relevance to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
